reviews.review_text: surprise, surprise The quality of the this aud will startle you. It's that good.Thanks to Pat Lee for recording. He says he switched off between songs to conserve his battery. So thanks also to Kevin Tobin for restoring the lost parts.
Money, money Best of three 'Money, money' played in that run consecutively. Sound quality is good and very much worth the listen.

Thanks to all involved in getting this up here. I seem to have lost my soundboard of the meat of this show.  Fortunately, this aud is quite listenable, although Bob and Keith do get a little lost in the mix at times.  Still, I can't give it fewer than 5 stars just on the strength of the Playin'.  This is not just music, it's EXPERIENCE.  

I don't always have 46 minutes to devote to one tune.  But this one has so many different sections to the jam, it's like several tunes wrapped into one big package.  Tonal, dissonant, quite and ethereal, or brutally manic meltdown -- it's all there.  If you don't have the patience to sit back and listen to this, if you prefer your jams in 10-15 minute rockin' chunks, then fine.  Put on something from 77 and on.  But if you're looking for a long-form exploratory jam, they don't get longer or more exploratory than this.

46 minute version of PITB The sound quality here is perfect. Very impressive audio. This entire show really blazes! 5 stars.

Thank you Kevin
